OL,3,CThe bears helping people from across
OL,4,Cthe country deal with trauma
OL,6,FThe group now has 6,000 members from
OL,7,Facross the world and has collectively
OL,8,Fprovided bears to the children
OL,9,Faffected by the fatal Southport
OL,10,Fstabbing attack in 2024, victims of
OL,11,Fthe war in Ukraine and many more.
OL,13,FMrs Pearce said "When the incident
OL,14,Fhappened in Southport last summer, I
OL,15,Fput a call out for bears as it was not
OL,16,Fjust the families that were affected
OL,17,Fby it, it was all the children that
OL,18,Flost their friends, so I thought it
OL,19,Fwould be a good idea to give a bear to
OL,20,Fchildren so that they had a friend,"
