OL,3,CThe bears helping people from across
OL,4,Cthe country deal with trauma
OL,6,FThe retired care manager continued "We
OL,7,Freceived thousands ` people were
OL,8,Fsending them to me from all over the
OL,9,FUK, and my husband and I went over to
OL,10,FSouthport and we went to a fire
OL,11,Fstation there, and a man who worked
OL,12,Fthere was overwhelmed with how many we
OL,13,Fgave.
OL,15,F"Fire service staff distributed the
OL,16,Fbears to other emergency services and
OL,17,Fschools in the area, an experience Mrs
OL,18,FPearce found "humbling".
